{{Definition
|Entry=Schema Relation Type
|Description=In the Wiki, schemas (both cogs and frames) are listed along with information that contextualizes and relates the schema to other schemas, either more generic schemas from which it inherits or related schemas which it commonly uses or is co-activated with. For instance, in the entry for the schema Motor_control, the related schema Action is listed. ''The current possible relation types are:'' 1. makes use of, 2. is a subcase/specific case/subschema of, and 3. is somehow related to.
|Utility=Wiki
|Entered by=Elise, 
