{{Definition
|Entry=Role
|Other Aliases=Schema role; Semantic roles; Frame role; Frame element
|Description=Schemas, both cogs and frames, are given roles (as many as are needed to understand the schema inferences, and as detailed as need be in terms of naming). When schemas appear in a metaphor mapping, the same roles as were listed for that schema in its schema form entry appear in the metaphor mapping. Generally, the roles are assigned names that make them maximally relevant to and reflective of the schema they are roles of, and maximally distinct from the more generic schema from which they inherit.
|Entered by=Elise, 
}}

{{Definition
|Entry=Specific Metaphor
|Description=While metaphors fall along a continuum when it comes to specificity, we may want to call 'specific metaphors' those metaphors which are the most specific metaphors for their cascade.
|Entered by=Elise, 
}}

{{Definition
