{{Definition |Entry=Family |Description=Each schema can (optionally) be specified to be a member of one or more Schema families. Similarly, each metaphor is (optionally) defined to be a member of one or more Metaphor families.
Families are used to group related schemas/metaphors together, e.g. for ease of analyzing a particular semantic domain or set of metaphors.
Lists of Schema Families and Metaphor Families can be accessed via links listed under the Metaphor Data Guide section of the Main page of the Wiki. Clicking on a given family name provides access to a list of the schemas/metaphors that have been specified to be members of that family, as well as a diagram that illustrates the defined relations between these schemas/metaphors. For schema families, there is also a list of the LUs associated with each of the schemas. |Applies to=Metaphor & Schema |Entered by=Ellen }}

{{Definition |Entry=Family |Description=Each schema can (optionally) be specified to be a member of one or more Schema families. Similarly, each metaphor is (optionally) defined to be a member of one or more Metaphor families.
Families are used to group related schemas/metaphors together, e.g. for ease of analyzing a particular semantic domain or set of metaphors.
