{{Definition |Entry=Binding |Description=A binding is a circuit that links two or more entities. Types of bindings include role-filler and entity-to-entity bindings (e.g., anaphora). There is also a binding between the entity created by the role-filler binding and a role in an x-schema.
Within Schema pages, the Bindings field is used to specify bindings between a given role in the current schema and one or more roles in the Schema(s) listed in the "Related Schemas" block. Dot notation is used to specify the Related schema role. And the binding relation itself is specified using a "=" sign.
E.g. if the current schema is "Self propelled motion" (which includes a 'self_mover' role), and a related schema is "Action" (which includes an 'actor' role), a relevant binding would be: self_mover = Action.actor |Applies to=Schema |Notation='''=''' |Entered by=Elise, |Last reviewed by=Ellen }}

