{{Definition
|Entry=Subcase of
|Other Aliases=Instance of; Special case of; Specific case of
|Description=Neurally, these are either subcircuits with a different connectivity or the same circuits activated at different times with different bindings. In terms of metaphors these are, for instance: THINKING IS MOVING is an instance of MIND IS A BODY, as is COMMUNICATING IS SHOWING, etc. What we now call instance was formerly called "special case of" in George's lectures and writings.
|Entered by=Elise, 
}}

{{Definition
|Entry=Subcase of
|Other Aliases=Instance of; Special case of; Specific case of
|Description=Neurally, these are either subcircuits with a different connectivity or the same circuits activated at different times with different bindings. In terms of metaphors these are, for instance: THINKING IS MOVING is an instance of MIND IS A BODY, as is COMMUNICATING IS SHOWING, etc. What we now call instance was formerly called "special case of" in George's lectures and writings.
