|Entry=Cultural Scope
|Description="Cultural scope" refers to which languages/cultures a schema or metaphor has been validated for. This includes both national-level information (e.g., American English) and within-culture information (e.g., American conservative, American progressive). Some schemas/metaphors do not hold across languages/cultures.
|Applies to=Metaphor & Schema
|Entered by=Elise,
